<item>
            <title>[LU-3004] MGS llog choke on to much parameter data</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3004</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In attempt to create a large stripe system with lvm I ran into a issue that prevented the MGT from mounting. The system has 4 OSS with 28 real disk but I used lvm to create 56 OST per OSS thus slicing the disk into 8 partitions to use. When I went to mount the file system the MGT refused to mount and gave the following error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; LustreError: 19657:0:(mgs_llog.c:1540:add_param()) params are too long:&lt;br/&gt;
failover.node=10.37.248.63@o2ib1 failover.node=10.37.248.64@o2ib1&lt;br/&gt;
failover.node=10.37.248.65@o2ib1 failover.node=10.37.248.62@o2ib1&lt;br/&gt;
